            <thetext>Please take another look at those demos. Thats really not the way we want to promote those features in our release notes. This demos should be featured so please put some extra love in them:

- hitting play increases the buttons size and reduces the padding to the next button to 0 or even less
- we have fitting icons for most of the controls so please use them
- there is no &quot;unmute&quot;... mute should be a toggle button which could be pressed or not
- the play buttons does not get back to play as soon as the media ended playing
- unloop is also not a good word if existant at all. We should also use a toggle button here
- show controls only works in the video demo. The audio demo only shows the controls as soon as the focus has been removed of the button. (Chrome)
- Controls are cut of in FF4 in the audio demo
- A total playtime would be nice e.g. in or somewhere around the progress bar
- Using the nativ controls does not reflect its state to the custom controls</thetext>
